items.title: Trump to ask DOJ to probe Jeffrey Epstein involvement with Clinton, JPMorgan, Summers
items.description: President Trump himself is a former longtime friend of sex offender Jeffrey Epstein, who killed himself in a federal jail during Trump's first term.

items.title: U.S. and Switzerland reach trade deal to lower tariffs to 15%
items.description: Switzerland has been subject to one of the highest tariff rates levied on an individual country by the Trump administration.

items.title: Goldman Sachs stands by top lawyer Kathy Ruemmler after her emails with Jeffrey Epstein exposed
items.description: The email chats between top lawyer Kathy Ruemmler and Jeffrey Epstein came years after his guilty plea to sex crimes in Florida.

items.title: Government shutdown back pay headed to federal workers in coming days
items.description: President Donald Trump late Wednesday signed a funding bill that reopened the U.S. government for the first time since it shut down on Oct. 1.

items.title: Trump signs funding bill, ends government shutdown
items.description: Most Democrats, who are in the minority in Congress, opposed the funding bill because it does not include extending enhanced ACA tax credits.
